    {
      "id": "1207479027952340",
      "score": 5,
      "review_title": "Moke Horror: perfections and flaws",
      "review_description": "When I had first downloaded moke horror, I wasn't expecting much other than a copy of animal company, but I could not have been more wrong. When I had loaded into the game, I was greeted by the nicest movement I had seen from one of these games in some time and very nice looking models. The things that this game  has done right heavily outweigh the cons. The game perfectly shows the things that chimplab did right and made those better, with great enemy models and the ability to outrun the enemies, although not for long. The Moke customization is an incredible feature being very dynamic. The ability to earn money in the game and also having an alternative money for cosmetics is an incredible feature to keep the players engaged and keep having things for them to look forward to in the shop instead of the grind of gorilla tag with nothing to look forward to other than tomorrow's rocks. Next, the option to be one of the enemies is one of the most creative ideas I've seen from one of these games by far, which also grants an incredibly easy way to gain coins. Now, the only flaw that I could point out is that the monsters are slightly too fast to be able to outrun and escape. Overall, the best gaming experience I've found in one of these \"gorilla tag inspired horror games\".",
      "date": 1764449379,
      "review_helpful_count": 42,
      "author_display_name": "TheHyacinth",
      "author_alias": "TheHyacinth",
      "developer_response": null
